                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-96-off526 t18291029-96-crimeloc529"></join>. On the 8th of October I was in my parlour, and saw the prisoner come and take a piece of bacon from my window, and walk away - I overtook him about thirty yards off; he threw the bacon down, and I took it up - this is the bacon: the shop window was open.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been out of employ, and was driven to distress; I had my goods seized, and had a wife and child to support.</p>
